<article id="post-1086" class="post-1086 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-rants tag-canadian tag-elections tag-human-rights tag-politics">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/09/conservatives-win-the-next-canadian-federal-election/" rel="bookmark">Conservatives win the next Canadian federal election!</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>This isn&#8217;t a predictive headline, folks. This is truth. The Conservatives will win the election in October. I, as an Expat, can&#8217;t vote in it, but that doesn&#8217;t mean that I don&#8217;t take at least a sense of interest in it. Or stock in the fact that the Conservatives are finally getting what they wanted the last time: Complete control.<br />
For the last two years, Canada has been living in the most blessed of political states: a minority government. As close to having the car in neutral as it gets. It means the least chance of political scandal (the &#8220;ruling&#8221; party doesn&#8217;t want to make mistakes that&#8217;ll haunt them come election time), and the opposition enjoys a place of perceived power as they get courted by the ruling party to help push through votes.<br />
Well, that&#8217;s all coming to an end now. So brace yourself, Canada &#8212; things are likely to get worse.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/09/conservatives-win-the-next-canadian-federal-election/#more-1086" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Conservatives win the next Canadian federal election!&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

