<article id="post-1029" class="post-1029 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-rants tag-beijing tag-china tag-human-rights tag-politics tag-sports">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/08/the-ioc-is-living-in-a-dream-world/" rel="bookmark">The IOC is living in a dream world</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>As I was skipping through my various feeds this morning, <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/othersports/olympics/2518676/Beijing-Olympics-George-Bush-calls-on-China-to-improve-human-rights-record.html">I came across the following quote</a> from Jacques Rogge, President of the IOC:</p>
<blockquote><p>Jacques Rogge, the president of the International Olympic Committee, said the Games would &#8220;help the world to understand China, and it will also help China to understand the world.&#8221;</p></blockquote>
<p>I think we need to send a team into the IOC&#8217;s fantasy world and extract them, because they&#8217;ve clearly (and totally) misunderstood the situation.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/08/the-ioc-is-living-in-a-dream-world/#more-1029" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;The IOC is living in a dream world&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

